nodes.text: This Quarren lived in Mos Eisley on the Planet Tatooine and was an associate of the Rodian bounty hunter Greedo during the Clone Wars.

Around 21 BBY, the Pantoran Chairman, Baron Notluwiski Papanoida, and his son Ion came to Jabba's Palace on Tatooine looking for Greedo, whom they suspected of kidnapping the chairman's daughters, Chi Eekway and Che Amanwe. The two found Greedo and brought him before Jabba the Hutt, where he confessed to kidnapping one of Papanoida's daughters that he held captive on Mos Eisley.

The three then left for Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina, the place where Greedo hid the senator's daughter. Once there, Greedo told a Weequay to go get the prisoner. Meanwhile, one of the bounty hunters that accompanied Greedo in his kidnapping earlier was also at the bar, talking to this Quarren. The bounty hunter soon grew suspicious when he noticed Greedo with Ion and Baron Papanoida, who pretended to be agents from the Trade Federation. Seconds after, the Weequay came back to the bar with Papanoida's daughter, who immediately called him "father" which destroyed his cover, causing massive bar shootout to ensue. This Quarren attempted to shoot Ion Papanoida, but was knocked unconscious when Che Amanwe hit him in the head with a bottle and stole his weapon.
This character is the only cantina patron to survive the shootout, with the exception of Greedo.
